{"name": "filez4eva", "metadata": {"name": "filez4eva", "version": "3.0.3", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11"], "home_page": "https://steamwiz.io", "license": "MIT", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["watchdog", "wizlib"], "summary": "Shift scans, photos, and other files into structured folders for permanent safekeeping", "upload_time": 1733889463}, "documentation": ["# Filez4Eva\n\nShift scans, photos, and other files into structured folders for permanent safekeeping\n---\n\n<a href=\"https://www.flaticon.com/free-icons/elephant\" title=\"elephant icons\">Elephant icon created by Flat Icons - Flaticon</a>\n\nI keep files named and organized in a certain way in DropBox. This tool names new files correctly and puts them in the right directory.\n\n## Installation\n\nIt's best to install using `pipx`. See [the pipx site](https://pypa.github.io/pipx/) if you need it. Then:\n\n```bash\npipx install filez4eva\n```\n\n## Usage\n\nThe directory pattern for account documents is:\n\n```\n~/Dropbox/accounts/<year>/<account>/<date>-<part>.<extension>\n```\n\nWhere:\n\n- `year` is the year of the document, typically from the date\n- `account` is the name of the account, all lower case, hyphen separated\n- `date` is the date on the document in `YYYYMMDD` format\n- `part` is the textual part of the name of the document, often starting with the account name, all lower case, hyphen separated\n- `extension` is the original filename extension, often `pdf`\n\nI have my browsers etc. set to download new files to Desktop, then it's easy to run Filez4Eva on a file on the desktop using tab completion.\n\n```\nfilez4eva ~/Desktop/123456789SomeFileIDownloaded.pdf\n```\n\nFilez4Eva will ask a series of questions, then move the file.\n\nNote the `part` supports tab-completion, where it looks up all the files previously stored under that account, in any year. So it's easy to reproduce names of periodic files such as financial statements or invoices.\n\n---\n\nCopyright (C) 2023 by Francis Potter. Licensed under the MIT license.\n\n"], "modules": [{"name": "filez4eva", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "filez4eva.Filez4EvaApp", "bases": ["WizApp"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "filez4eva.Filez4EvaApp.base", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "filez4eva.Filez4EvaApp.name", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "filez4eva.Filez4EvaApp.handlers", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}], "exports": [{"name": "filez4eva.ConfigHandler", "xref": {"fqname": "wizlib.config_handler.ConfigHandler", "project": "wizlib"}}, {"name": "filez4eva.Filez4EvaCommand", "xref": {"fqname": "filez4eva.command.Filez4EvaCommand", "project": null}}, {"name": "filez4eva.StreamHandler", "xref": {"fqname": "wizlib.stream_handler.StreamHandler", "project": "wizlib"}}, {"name": "filez4eva.UIHandler", "xref": {"fqname": "wizlib.ui_handler.UIHandler", "project": "wizlib"}}, {"name": "filez4eva.WizApp", "xref": {"fqname": "wizlib.app.WizApp", "project": "wizlib"}}]}, {"name": "filez4eva.error", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "filez4eva.error.Filez4EvaError", "bases": ["Exception"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}], "exports": []}, {"name": "filez4eva.__main__", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "filez4eva.command", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "filez4eva.command.Filez4EvaCommand", "bases": ["WizCommand"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "filez4eva.command.Filez4EvaCommand.default", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}], "exports": [{"name":